                     "topFinding":  "The three perf-pass releases since the last review (v0.99.16-v0.99.18) landed real wins on the project\u0027s one standing engineering exposure: the v0.99.17 spatial hash removed the O(units x enemies) and O(defenders x enemies) targeting scans, closing the carryover O(n) scale findings, and v0.99.16 cleared the minimap/fog/nav per-frame allocations, so performance rose 74 to 82 and scale-architecture 62 to 75. The remaining render ceiling (34 fps at 2000 enemies on the per-Node skinned-FBX path) is now a deliberate owner-gated decision, not an open task: v0.99.18 parked the crowd3d MultiMesh fix behind a default-off use_crowd3d toggle because it trades enemy walk animation for static instancing, a look call for the owner, so it moves to deferred. Everything else is unchanged: the hygiene backlog the deep 06-28 pass surfaced (stale project metadata, public-voice tells in the GDD changelog, asset license/provenance gaps, the orphaned save_load autoload) carries forward intact because no commit touched those files. No hard rule is breached, so there is no BLOCK; verdict stays in-progress with the open-action count down from 13 to 12 and the bar-raise loop demonstrably recovered after its 06-26/-27 gap.",
